  <mainDescription>&lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        &lt;img style=&quot;HEIGHT: 150px; WIDTH: 500px&quot; alt=&quot;Monitoring&quot; src=&quot;resources/monitoring.png&quot; />&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defined metrics as throughput, response time, hits per second must be monitored during test execution as well as&#xD;
    bottlenecks identification.&lt;br />&#xD;
    This monitoring allows performance testing roles to obtain outputs for subsequent phases, analysis and reporting in&#xD;
    post-test stage.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The monitoring phase has a strong connection with the execution phase, in some cases they get confused, because some&#xD;
    tools execute and do the monitoring simultaneously.&lt;br />&#xD;
    However, we find it interesting to have this separation due to the degree of importance that both phases have in the&#xD;
    performance test.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
